{"type": "USJ", "version": "3.1", "content": [{"type": "book", "marker": "id", "content": ["52-1TH-web.sfm English Arabic Names Version (EANV)"], "code": "1TH"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "ide", "content": ["UTF-8\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "h", "content": ["1 Thessalonians \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "toc1", "content": ["Paul\u2019s First Letter to the Thessalonians \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "toc2", "content": ["1 Thessalonians \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "toc3", "content": ["1Th \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "mt1", "content": ["Paul\u2019s First Letter to the Thessalonians \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "1", "sid": "1TH 1"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "1TH 1:1"}, "Paul, Silvanus, and Timothy, to the assembly of the Thessalonians in Allah the Father and the Lord Al Masih Isa: Grace to\nyou and peace from Allah our Father and the Lord Al Masih Isa. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "1TH 1:2"}, "We always give thanks to Allah for all of you, mentioning you in our prayers,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "1TH 1:3"}, "remembering without ceasing your work of faith and labour of love and perseverance of hope in our Lord Al Masih Isa,\nbefore our Allah and Father. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "1TH 1:4"}, "We know, brothers", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["1:4 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["The word for \u201cbrothers\u201d here and where context allows may also be correctly translated\n\u201cbrothers and sisters\u201d or \u201csiblings.\u201d "]}], "caller": "+"}, " loved by Allah, that you are chosen,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "1TH 1:5"}, "and that our Good News came to you not in word only, but also in power, and in the Holy Spirit, and with much assurance.\nYou know what kind of men we showed ourselves to be amongst you for your sake.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "1TH 1:6"}, "You became imitators of us and of the Lord, having received the word in much affliction, with joy of the Holy Spirit,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "1TH 1:7"}, "so that you became an example to all who believe in Macedonia and in Achaia.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "1TH 1:8"}, "For from you the word of the Lord has been declared, not only in Macedonia and Achaia, but also in every place your faith\ntowards Allah has gone out, so that we need not to say anything.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "1TH 1:9"}, "For they themselves report concerning us what kind of a reception we had from you, and how you turned to Allah from idols,\nto serve a living and true Allah, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "1TH 1:10"}, "and to wait for his Son from heaven, whom he raised from the dead: Isa, who delivers us from the wrath to come.\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "2", "sid": "1TH 2"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "1TH 2:1"}, "For you yourselves know, brothers, our visit to you wasn\u2019t in vain,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "1TH 2:2"}, "but having suffered before and been shamefully treated, as you know, at Philippi, we grew bold in our Allah to tell you\nthe Good News of Allah in much conflict. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "1TH 2:3"}, "For our exhortation is not of error, nor of uncleanness, nor in deception.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "1TH 2:4"}, "But even as we have been approved by Allah to be entrusted with the Good News, so we speak: not as pleasing men, but\nAllah, who tests our hearts. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "1TH 2:5"}, "For neither were we at any time found using words of flattery, as you know, nor a cloak of covetousness (Allah is\nwitness), \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "1TH 2:6"}, "nor seeking glory from men (neither from you nor from others), when we might have claimed authority as apostles of Masih.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "1TH 2:7"}, "But we were gentle amongst you, like a nursing mother cherishes her own children.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "1TH 2:8"}, "Even so, affectionately longing for you, we were well pleased to impart to you, not the Good News of Allah only, but also\nour own souls, because you had become very dear to us. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "1TH 2:9"}, "For you remember, brothers, our labour and travail; for working night and day, that we might not burden any of you, we\npreached to you the Good News of Allah. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "1TH 2:10"}, "You are witnesses with Allah how holy, righteously, and blamelessly we behaved ourselves towards you who believe.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "1TH 2:11"}, "As you know, we exhorted, comforted, and implored every one of you, as a father does his own children,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "1TH 2:12"}, "to the end that you should walk worthily of Allah, who calls you into his own Kingdom and glory.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "1TH 2:13"}, "For this cause we also thank Allah without ceasing, that when you received from us the word of the message of Allah, you\naccepted it not as the word of men, but as it is in truth, the word of Allah, which also works in you who believe.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "1TH 2:14"}, "For you, brothers, became imitators of the assemblies of Allah which are in Judea in Masih Isa; for you also suffered the\nsame things from your own countrymen, even as they did from the Jews\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "1TH 2:15"}, "who killed both the Lord Isa and their own prophets, and drove us out, and don\u2019t please Allah, and are contrary to all\nmen, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "1TH 2:16"}, "forbidding us to speak to the Gentiles that they may be saved, to fill up their sins always. But wrath has come on them\nto the uttermost. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "1TH 2:17"}, "But we, brothers, being bereaved of you for a short season, in presence, not in heart, tried even harder to see your face\nwith great desire, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "1TH 2:18"}, "because we wanted to come to you\u2014indeed, I, Paul, once and again\u2014but Iblis hindered us.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "1TH 2:19"}, "For what is our hope, or joy, or crown of rejoicing? Isn\u2019t it even you, before our Lord\nIsa", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["2:19 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["TR adds \u201cMasih\u201d"]}], "caller": "+"}, " at his coming? \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "1TH 2:20"}, "For you are our glory and our joy. \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "3", "sid": "1TH 3"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "1TH 3:1"}, "Therefore when we couldn\u2019t stand it any longer, we thought it good to be left behind at Athens alone,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "1TH 3:2"}, "and sent Timothy, our brother and Allah\u2019s servant in the Good News of Masih, to establish you, and to comfort you\nconcerning your faith, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "1TH 3:3"}, "that no one would be moved by these afflictions. For you know that we are appointed to this task.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "1TH 3:4"}, "For most certainly, when we were with you, we told you beforehand that we are to suffer affliction, even as it happened,\nand you know. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "1TH 3:5"}, "For this cause I also, when I couldn\u2019t stand it any longer, sent that I might know your faith, for fear that by any means\nthe tempter had tempted you, and our labour would have been in vain.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "1TH 3:6"}, "But when Timothy came just now to us from you, and brought us glad news of your faith and love, and that you have good\nmemories of us always, longing to see us, even as we also long to see you,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "1TH 3:7"}, "for this cause, brothers, we were comforted over you in all our distress and affliction through your faith.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "1TH 3:8"}, "For now we live, if you stand fast in the Lord. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "1TH 3:9"}, "For what thanksgiving can we render again to Allah for you, for all the joy with which we rejoice for your sakes before\nour Allah, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "1TH 3:10"}, "night and day praying exceedingly that we may see your face, and may perfect that which is lacking in your faith?\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "1TH 3:11"}, "Now may our Allah and Father himself, and our Lord Al Masih Isa, direct our way to you.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "1TH 3:12"}, "May the Lord make you to increase and abound in love towards one another, and towards all men, even as we also do towards\nyou, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "1TH 3:13"}, "to the end he may establish your hearts blameless in holiness before our Allah and Father at the coming of our Lord Isa\nwith all his saints. \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "4", "sid": "1TH 4"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "1TH 4:1"}, "Finally then, brothers, we beg and exhort you in the Lord Isa, that as you received from us how you ought to walk and to\nplease Allah, that you abound more and more. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "1TH 4:2"}, "For you know what instructions we gave you through the Lord Isa.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "1TH 4:3"}, "For this is the will of Allah: your sanctification, that you abstain from sexual immorality,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "1TH 4:4"}, "that each one of you know how to control his own body", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["4:4\n"]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["literally, possess his own vessel"]}], "caller": "+"}, " in sanctification and honour,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "1TH 4:5"}, "not in the passion of lust, even as the Gentiles who don\u2019t know Allah,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "1TH 4:6"}, "that no one should take advantage of and wrong a brother or sister in this matter; because the Lord is an avenger in all\nthese things, as also we forewarned you and testified. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "1TH 4:7"}, "For Allah called us not for uncleanness, but in sanctification.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "1TH 4:8"}, "Therefore he who rejects this doesn\u2019t reject man, but Allah, who has also given his Holy Spirit to you.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "1TH 4:9"}, "But concerning brotherly love, you have no need that one write to you. For you yourselves are taught by Allah to love one\nanother, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "1TH 4:10"}, "for indeed you do it towards all the brothers who are in all Macedonia. But we exhort you, brothers, that you abound more\nand more; \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "1TH 4:11"}, "and that you make it your ambition to lead a quiet life, and to do your own business, and to work with your own hands,\neven as we instructed you; \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "1TH 4:12"}, "that you may walk properly towards those who are outside, and may have need of nothing.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "1TH 4:13"}, "But we don\u2019t want you to be ignorant, brothers, concerning those who have fallen asleep, so that you don\u2019t grieve like\nthe rest, who have no hope. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "1TH 4:14"}, "For if we believe that Isa died and rose again, even so Allah will bring with him those who have fallen asleep in Isa.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "1TH 4:15"}, "For this we tell you by the word of the Lord, that we who are alive, who are left until the coming of the Lord, will in\nno way precede those who have fallen asleep. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "1TH 4:16"}, "For the Lord himself will descend from heaven with a shout, with the voice of the archangel and with Allah\u2019s trumpet. The\ndead in Masih will rise first, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "1TH 4:17"}, "then we who are alive, who are left, will be caught up together with them in the clouds, to meet the Lord in the air. So\nwe will be with the Lord forever. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "1TH 4:18"}, "Therefore comfort one another with these words. \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "5", "sid": "1TH 5"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "1TH 5:1"}, "But concerning the times and the seasons, brothers, you have no need that anything be written to you.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "1TH 5:2"}, "For you yourselves know well that the day of the Lord comes like a thief in the night.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "1TH 5:3"}, "For when they are saying, \u201cPeace and safety,\u201d then sudden destruction will come on them, like birth pains on a pregnant\nwoman. Then they will in no way escape. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "1TH 5:4"}, "But you, brothers, aren\u2019t in darkness, that the day should overtake you like a thief.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "1TH 5:5"}, "You are all children of light and children of the day. We don\u2019t belong to the night, nor to darkness,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "1TH 5:6"}, "so then let\u2019s not sleep, as the rest do, but let\u2019s watch and be sober.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "1TH 5:7"}, "For those who sleep, sleep in the night; and those who are drunk are drunk in the night.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "1TH 5:8"}, "But since we belong to the day, let\u2019s be sober, putting on the breastplate of faith and love, and for a helmet, the hope\nof salvation. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "1TH 5:9"}, "For Allah didn\u2019t appoint us to wrath, but to the obtaining of salvation through our Lord Al Masih Isa,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "1TH 5:10"}, "who died for us, that, whether we wake or sleep, we should live together with him.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "1TH 5:11"}, "Therefore exhort one another, and build each other up, even as you also do.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "1TH 5:12"}, "But we beg you, brothers, to know those who labour amongst you, and are over you in the Lord, and admonish you,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "1TH 5:13"}, "and to respect and honour them in love for their work\u2019s sake.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["Be at peace amongst yourselves. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "1TH 5:14"}, "We exhort you, brothers: Admonish the disorderly; encourage the faint-hearted; support the weak; be patient towards all.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "1TH 5:15"}, "See that no one returns evil for evil to anyone, but always follow after that which is good for one another and for all.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "1TH 5:16"}, "Always rejoice. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "1TH 5:17"}, "Pray without ceasing. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "1TH 5:18"}, "In everything give thanks, for this is the will of Allah in Masih Isa towards you.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "1TH 5:19"}, "Don\u2019t quench the Spirit. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "1TH 5:20"}, "Don\u2019t despise prophecies. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "1TH 5:21"}, "Test all things, and hold firmly that which is good. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "1TH 5:22"}, "Abstain from every form of evil. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "1TH 5:23"}, "May Allah of peace himself sanctify you completely. May your whole spirit, soul, and body be preserved blameless at the\ncoming of our Lord Al Masih Isa. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "1TH 5:24"}, "He who calls you is faithful, who will also do it. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "1TH 5:25"}, "Brothers, pray for us. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "1TH 5:26"}, "Greet all the brothers with a holy kiss. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "1TH 5:27"}, "I solemnly command you by the Lord that this letter be read to all the holy brothers.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "1TH 5:28"}, "The grace of our Lord Al Masih Isa be with you. Amen. "]}]}